      • isComplete

        public boolean isComplete()
        Description copied from interface: StreamedQueryResult
        Returns whether the StreamedQueryResult is complete.

        A StreamedQueryResult is complete if the HTTP connection associated with this query has been ended gracefully. Once complete, the StreamedQueryResult will continue to deliver any remaining rows, then call onComplete() on the subscriber, if present.

        Specified by:
        isComplete in interface StreamedQueryResult
        Overrides:

      • isFailed

        public boolean isFailed()
        Description copied from interface: StreamedQueryResult
        Returns whether the StreamedQueryResult is failed.

        A StreamedQueryResult is failed if an error is received from the server. Once failed, onError() is called on the subscriber, if present, any existing poll() calls will return null, and new calls to StreamedQueryResult.poll() and subscribe() will be rejected.

        Specified by:
        isFailed in interface StreamedQueryResult
        Overrides:
